    <div class="px-4 py-2">

        <h2 class="pt-4">Who Is Jimmy Broadbent?</h2>
        <br />
        <p>
            Jimmy Broadbent is a British sim racer, content creator, and motorsport enthusiast known for his engaging YouTube channel and charismatic commentary. Often referred to as “the shed man,” he became popular for streaming races and showcasing various sim racing titles from his converted garden shed studio.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-4" />
        <div class="p-3 my-3" style="background-image: url('https://mozaracing.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/2-1024x576.png'); background-size: cover; background-repeat: no-repeat; color:darkblue">
            <h2 class="pt-4">Content and Career</h2>
            <br />
            <ul>
                <li><strong>YouTube Channel:</strong> Over 900k subscribers as of 2025, featuring sim gameplay, racing challenges, and real-life vlogs.</li>
                <li><strong>Real Racing:</strong> Competed in the <em>Praga Cup</em>, <em>British Endurance Championship</em>, and multiple real-world racing events.</li>
                <li><strong>Sim Platforms:</strong> Regularly features iRacing, Assetto Corsa, rFactor 2, Automobilista, and more.</li>
                <li><strong>Advocacy:</strong> Promotes accessibility and fun over elitism in the sim racing community.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <hr class="my-4" />

        <h2 class="pt-4">Why He's Loved</h2>
        <br />
        <p>
            Jimmy blends relatable humor with genuine racing skill. Whether he's struggling in an impossible challenge or battling for a win in a virtual endurance race, he brings charm and personality to every moment.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-4" />

        <h2 class="pt-4">Impact on the Community</h2>
        <br />
        <p>
            Jimmy has helped popularize sim racing for thousands of newcomers by showing that it's not just for pros or hardcore tech setups. His entertaining yet educational approach has introduced many to platforms like iRacing, ACC, and rFactor 2.
        </p>
        <p>
            He’s also a frequent collaborator with brands, sim hardware companies, and other influencers, bridging the gap between casual fans and competitive sim racing.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-4" />

        <h2 class="pt-4">Fun Facts</h2>
        <br />
        <ul>
            <li>Started streaming in a literal garden shed, now races real cars.</li>
            <li>Famous for quotes like "SEND IT!" and his love-hate relationship with the Nürburgring.</li>
            <li>Has a dedicated fanbase known for memes, loyalty, and "The Shed" lore.</li>
        </ul>

